begin_5503510e	"Friendly Stranger"	Hey what's up - you new to the neighborhood?	game/script.rpy	282	"Friendly Stranger" "[what]"
begin_e4863cda	"Friendly Stranger"	Welcome to the neighborhood! I live right down the street.	game/script.rpy	286	"Friendly Stranger" "[what]"
begin_06da6ccc	"Friendly Stranger"	I dunno where you moved from, but we don't do the whole 'mysterious stranger' thing here.	game/script.rpy	288	"Friendly Stranger" "[what]"
begin_5e9fe8e7	"Friendly Stranger"	Anyway, I'm glad you're here, new kid.	game/script.rpy	289	"Friendly Stranger" "[what]"
begin_f92a9b23	el	I'm Elliot. I'm hoping you'll help me convince Mayor Watson not to sell our lot to those parking guys.	game/script.rpy	290	el "[what]"
parkingguys_26899442	el	That guy over there in the suit is from CityPark. They want to turn our empty lot into a big parking [structure] for the neighborhood.	game/script.rpy	298	el "[what]"
parkingguys_d8ac5a89	el	But me and the other Community Gardeners have been trying to convince Mayor Watson to donate the lot to our food justice project instead.	game/script.rpy	299	el "[what]"
parkingguys_63f8d405	el	The parking [structure] makes money, but a community garden would be huge for this neighborhood!	game/script.rpy	300	el "[what]"
parkingguys_47ada2e0	t	Hey! Sorry to interrupt - but this seems like a good time to show you your notebook!	game/script.rpy	305	t "[what]"
parkingguys_e0d9612f	t	See the + button to the left? This automatically adds whatever is being said to your notebook!	game/script.rpy	307	t "[what]"
parkingguys_8a50f008	t	If you want to open your notebook and see what notes you've taken, you can click on the Notes button in the top right!	game/script.rpy	308	t "[what]"
parkingguys_53b6aefe	t	You can edit notes you've taken, or write your own custom notes! You can also delete notes you don't want.	game/script.rpy	309	t "[what]"
parkingguys_63d3479d	t	Hope that helps!	game/script.rpy	310	t "[what]"
parkingguys_08c722ce	el	Whoa, a bee just flew past your face! You know, I bet if we built a garden here, the bees would love it.	game/script.rpy	315	el "[what]"
parkingguys_c959488d	el	The garden would be great for people too. The nearest grocery store is miles away, and most folks don't have a car.	game/script.rpy	316	el "[what]"
explain_problem_b9d5db23	el	Our food justice project needs space to build a community garden in our neighborhood, so that folks here can grow fresh food that doesn't cost so much.	game/script.rpy	332	el "[what]"
explain_problem_c82984f8	el	Gardens are awesome, obviously, but for some reason the Mayor says he wants to see data about the benefits before making a decision.	game/script.rpy	333	el "[what]"
explain_problem_442f6aaa	el	I'm trying to gather some evidence to convince him, but I could really use some help.	game/script.rpy	334	el "[what]"
agreement_15c98b85	el	Awesome! I really appreciate it.	game/script.rpy	344	el "[what]"
foodjusticeexplain_186cdd7e	el	Food justice is this idea that everybody deserves access to healthy food that they can afford.	game/script.rpy	348	el "[what]"
foodjusticeexplain_24c3c237	el	Food in our community should also include stuff that makes sense for each person's culture, because not everyone eats the same kinds of foods.	game/script.rpy	349	el "[what]"
foodjusticeexplain_02f72068	el	So many people in the U.S. only have access to fast-food restaurants, gas station food, and other places that sell food that is super processed.	game/script.rpy	350	el "[what]"
foodjusticeexplain_3c65c0b8	el	There's nothing wrong with eating that food sometimes, but if that's the only kind of food people in your neighborhood can buy that is affordable, then everyone has more trouble eating healthy and feeling good.	game/script.rpy	351	el "[what]"
talk_later_54a96741	el	If you're interested, you should go talk with the Community Gardeners. Wes and Nadia, the head gardeners, are over at Westgate Community Garden on the other side of the city.	game/script.rpy	360	el "[what]"
talk_later_50d65081	el	It would be so great if we could have a garden like that in our neighborhood! They even have beehives!	game/script.rpy	361	el "[what]"
talk_later_2cea9e17	el	You can also check out the science lab, where my friend Riley has been hanging out to learn about food science.	game/script.rpy	362	el "[what]"
foodlab_6e064d56	narrator	You step into a bustling room full of scientific equipment. A woman in a lab coat is currently sorting vials on a nearby counter.	game/script.rpy	390	narrator "[what]"
foodlab_3f36174b	narrator	Over by the table, another person is sorting papers and taking notes. You see brightly colored posters that read 'Community Gardeners'.	game/script.rpy	391	narrator "[what]"
labregular_f1e5e3c7	narrator	Click the person you want to talk to, or click the map to travel somewhere else.	game/script.rpy	397	narrator "[what]"
riley_1_440b30cb	r	Hi there! Elliot texted me and said he recruited you to help us gather notes for the Southport garden project.	game/script.rpy	414	r "[what]"
rileyintro_fef29886	r	We're so grateful for your help! I'm Riley. I'm a member of the Community Gardeners.	game/script.rpy	418	r "[what]"
rileyintro_ed0f4082	r	My job is to advocate for the neighborhood and write persuasive proposals to help us get things we need for the community.	game/script.rpy	419	r "[what]"
rileyintro_1d4173cb	r	Sometimes the city's budget office forgets about the important things, like green spaces where we can breathe fresh air.	game/script.rpy	420	r "[what]"
rileyintro_08177fe8	r	What do you think about the empty lot?	game/script.rpy	421	r "[what]"
riley_support_3bdf5685	r	It really is! I'm glad we're on the same page. Elliot knew you'd be a great addition to our team.	game/script.rpy	432	r "[what]"
riley_support_ad862b8f	r	Now we just need to figure out how to make sure the Mayor gets it, too. Do you have any ideas for how to convince him?	game/script.rpy	433	r "[what]"
long_intro_aea99336	r	I'm the director of a nonprofit organization called CareWorks. We advocate for the needs of our neighborhood by setting up programs that help the people here.	game/script.rpy	446	r "[what]"
long_intro_ca46b540	r	We help run things like community food pantries and after-school activities for kids. My work with the Community Gardeners is part of that!	game/script.rpy	447	r "[what]"
long_intro_9d9b2d41	r	We do research to help present proposals to the City, so that we can convince them to use money and resources in ways that will help our community grow.	game/script.rpy	448	r "[what]"
long_intro_a3aff997	r	I'd love your help gathering notes to improve our persuasive writing about why community gardens matter! We're going to share it with the Mayor when we're ready.	game/script.rpy	449	r "[what]"
long_intro_fcd188cc	r	There are several other community gardens in the city, but they're all pretty far from this neighborhood, and folks here could really use a reliable source of fresh food.	game/script.rpy	450	r "[what]"
riley_against_af548af8	r	Oh really? I'm curious why you think that.	game/script.rpy	461	r "[what]"
riley_against_fac46fdd	r	Alright, maybe you'll think of a reason later.	game/script.rpy	464	r "[what]"
riley_against_edbc0437	r	Hmm. That's fair. I still think the garden has more benefits for the people and the environment, but that's worth considering.	game/script.rpy	468	r "[what]"
riley_against_1f36b2bf	r	The government often relies on data and algorithms. But some things, like the value of a community garden, can't be measured in money alone. It's measured in how it helps empower the people who live here.	game/script.rpy	469	r "[what]"
riley_plan_d46634e4	r	I bet if we work together we can make a presentation so persuasive that it blows the socks off the Mayor and runs CityPark right out of town.	game/script.rpy	482	r "[what]"
riley_plan_fd06abbf	r	I'd love to hear your ideas!	game/script.rpy	483	r "[what]"
riley_plan_2423fe70	r	Sweet. What do you think we should say to convince the Mayor that a community garden is good for the neighborhood?	game/script.rpy	487	r "[what]"
ca_eval_riley_94a681c6	r	No worries. We can brainstorm when you're ready.	game/script.rpy	499	r "[what]"
ca_eval_riley_0ec17e62	r	Are there other ideas you want to run by me?	game/script.rpy	536	r "[what]"
ca_eval_riley_5dcfe669	r	Okay! Let me know if I can help as you gather more notes.	game/script.rpy	542	r "[what]"
not_convinced_399270d3	r	Hey, I'm used to convincing skeptical people. Don't you worry! I bet if you talk to folks around town and hear what they have to say, you might see it a little differently.	game/script.rpy	547	r "[what]"
bye_riley2_b91bdffb	r	Awesome! If you want to run any ideas by me before you talk to the Mayor, I'd be happy to help you workshop your argument. See ya!	game/script.rpy	553	r "[what]"
riley_2_013d2251	r	Back again! I'm glad. What's up?	game/script.rpy	561	r "[what]"
riley_2_d7137b03	r	Amazing! What ideas have you found about how we should use the empty lot?	game/script.rpy	569	r "[what]"
ca_foodjustice_5b8eb336	r	Oh, all sorts of things! What are you curious about?	game/script.rpy	575	r "[what]"
foodknowledge_loop_a4b4d885	r	Anything else you'd like to know?	game/script.rpy	638	r "[what]"
foodknowledge_loop_d7137b03	r	Amazing! What ideas have you found about how we should use the empty lot?	game/script.rpy	646	r "[what]"
foodknowledge_57ee2c1a	r	No worries. Ask me again anytime.	game/script.rpy	654	r "[what]"
byeriley_301be4a7	r	Keep doing great things! I'll be here if you need me.	game/script.rpy	680	r "[what]"
amara_1_f617990b	a	Hi! I'm Amara - I'm the lead scientist here at the food lab. Great to meet you.	game/script.rpy	698	a "[what]"
foodscientist_3482d4ce	a	Food scientists use chemistry, biology, and other sciences to study and analyze nutritional content like protein, fats, and vitamins.	game/script.rpy	720	a "[what]"
foodscientist_f1fe3bfb	a	We look at food quality, how to make nutrients last longer, and what causes food go bad. It can really help with making processed foods safe and healthy.	game/script.rpy	721	a "[what]"
foodscientist_f34587e9	a	So, basically, our aim is to help everyone have fresh, safe, and nutritious food.	game/script.rpy	722	a "[what]"
garden_info_492e34e4	a	The neighborhood has been buzzing with discussion about the empty lot and that parking company that wants to buy it up.	game/script.rpy	727	a "[what]"
garden_info_f4de51bb	a	From a food scientist's perspective, I really hope the Mayor supports the community garden.	game/script.rpy	728	a "[what]"
garden_info_db02b56d	a	I knew I liked you!	game/script.rpy	736	a "[what]"
reasons_d76bb9e3	a	People without local produce markets or community gardens mostly have to rely on shipped and preserved food.	game/script.rpy	740	a "[what]"
reasons_7181e43f	a	Shipping food isn't bad, necessarily, but it makes getting fresh, healthy food more complicated.	game/script.rpy	741	a "[what]"
reasons_82940d5e	a	In order to ship food from different places, you need to process the food to preserve its taste and prevent it from going bad.	game/script.rpy	742	a "[what]"
reasons_496a44ff	a	We usually freeze, cook, or can foods, or add some chemicals, which are also known as food additives.	game/script.rpy	743	a "[what]"
reasons_f4029050	a	When we process food, the food loses some nutrients and often ends up having high levels of sugar, salt, and fat, and not all food additives are good for our bodies.	game/script.rpy	744	a "[what]"
reasons_93c15771	a	That means if we only have access to shipped foods, we might have issues with lack of nutrition or we might eat too much of these unhealthy food additives.	game/script.rpy	745	a "[what]"
reasons_97f1b734	a	Anyway, a community garden doesn't fix everything, but it gives the people in the neighborhood another option for how to get affordable, fresh food.	game/script.rpy	746	a "[what]"
lab_stuff_38d0d0fc	a	I research things about food, how it grows, and how our bodies use it.	game/script.rpy	751	a "[what]"
lab_stuff_e93d09dc	a	When I was younger, I got so interested in food, especially fruits and vegetables that have a variety of colors.	game/script.rpy	752	a "[what]"
lab_stuff_7562ec52	a	Did you know that fruits and vegetables with different colors usually provide our bodies with different kinds of nutrients?	game/script.rpy	753	a "[what]"
lab_stuff_c3cc6af1	a	Those are the kinds of things I explore in my lab - what kinds of nutrients different foods have, and how to make sure foods are safe and healthy for our bodies.	game/script.rpy	754	a "[what]"
bye_amara_8e82d3a4	a	Oh okay! Well you're welcome to hang out, let me know if you get curious about anything!	game/script.rpy	759	a "[what]"
amara_2_2121e088	a	Hey there! What are you up to?	game/script.rpy	768	a "[what]"
amara_revisit_423cb091	a	Oh, I'm full of facts. Maybe I can help!	game/script.rpy	774	a "[what]"
sciencequestions_07f25761	a	What are you curious about?	game/script.rpy	784	a "[what]"
genetics_85de0998	a	Oh, plant genetics are so interesting. Like people, plants have DNA that carries information about the different kinds of traits they have.	game/script.rpy	801	a "[what]"
genetics_62b6a234	a	And just like with people, diversity makes plants stronger. Genetic diversity means that plants have lots of unique traits, so that a pest or weather change that harms one plant might not bother another.	game/script.rpy	802	a "[what]"
genetics_20f808ff	a	When our local ecosystem has a large variety of plants with diverse genetics, the overall ecosystem is healthier and more resilient.	game/script.rpy	803	a "[what]"
genetics2_7aee4dc3	a	Okay! So the thing with big farms and genetic diversity is that many of them like to pick the strongest and best-producing plants to grow over and over.	game/script.rpy	813	a "[what]"
genetics2_bb2e5210	a	For example, if all the big farms choose to grow the same type of strawberry plant because it grows big berries, then we start to lose some of the interesting local varieties that might be smaller, but have unique flavors or taste extra sweet.	game/script.rpy	814	a "[what]"
genetics2_70b8ed40	a	Someday the big strawberry plant might not be able to grow very well as our environment changes, so we need to protect genetic diversity to protect our future food system!	game/script.rpy	815	a "[what]"
soil_87e80381	a	Soil is super important for the health of plants. Dirt just looks like dirt at first glance, but there are actually 14 different nutrients in the soil that can change how plants grow.	game/script.rpy	819	a "[what]"
soil_807507fc	a	Different plants need different amounts of nutrients, but they all need the same ones - the big ones are nitrogen, phosphorus, and potassium. But calcium, magnesium, and sulfur are important too.	game/script.rpy	820	a "[what]"
soil_c112ec56	a	It's very important to keep track of the nutrients in the soil, because healthier soil can grow stronger plants, more food, and in some cases even healthier food.	game/script.rpy	821	a "[what]"
soil2_9ba41824	a	Some people like to grow their own food, because then they can be in control of the soil quality and the kinds of pesticides that are used on the food they eat.	game/script.rpy	831	a "[what]"
soil2_7b5674b1	a	Learning to grow your own food can also help to teach people useful skills and knowledge about food science, health, and farming pratices!	game/script.rpy	832	a "[what]"
environment_b97a2290	a	For the ecosystem, gardens give insects and animals a home. They provide food for pollinators and can be especially helpful if they're full of native plants.	game/script.rpy	836	a "[what]"
environment_b3991567	a	For our air, gardens help to filter pollution, especially if you have large plants like trees that can filter out lots of pollutants. Plants also produce oxygen for us to breathe.	game/script.rpy	837	a "[what]"
environment_324a073c	a	Local gardens also let us grow food that doesn't need to be driven a long way in order to get to us - so they help to make our food system more sustainable.	game/script.rpy	838	a "[what]"
environment2_0f2b9dfc	a	Food systems are so big and complex, and there isn't just one right answer for how to get healthy food to people and how to do it well. But I love complicated problems! That's why I'm a scientist.	game/script.rpy	848	a "[what]"
environment2_df466e99	a	And every family is different - sometimes our family recipes need ingredients that aren't easy to find in the grocery store.	game/script.rpy	849	a "[what]"
environment2_3a65f9db	a	So we should ask ourselves: how do we make sure everyone can find the foods they need and want, so that everyone has a voice in how they grow and buy their food?	game/script.rpy	850	a "[what]"
parkingquestions_9191f778	a	Ah, so you're curious about how the parking [structure] will impact the neighborhood?	game/script.rpy	854	a "[what]"
parkingquestions_6b6b51ed	a	I mostly study food, so I don't know a ton about the economic impact of parking [structure]s or how cars change the environment.	game/script.rpy	855	a "[what]"
parkingquestions_5f433799	a	Wes might know more - he did a lot of that research when he was building the Westgate community garden!	game/script.rpy	856	a "[what]"
byeamara_06cc7312	a	Have a great day! Let me know if I can help with your research.	game/script.rpy	861	a "[what]"
