victor_chatting_fb850380	v	Hi, I'm Victor. I just moved here a few months ago. Great to meet you!	game/script.rpy	903	v "[what]"
victor_chatting_f3919038	v	There's a really delicious soup from my hometown that I've been craving ever since I moved.	game/script.rpy	904	v "[what]"
victor_chatting_cb3d191b	v	But the grocery stores here don't sell the kinds of vegetables that my family uses to make the soup extra flavorful and special.	game/script.rpy	905	v "[what]"
victor_chatting_c36c0d71	v	I really want to make a soup that tastes like home. I wonder if the community gardeners would let me grow my own vegetables here?	game/script.rpy	906	v "[what]"
victor_chatting_4dbcddc7	v	I don't even have a balcony at my apartment, much less a yard. But maybe if I lived near a garden, I could learn how to grow things.	game/script.rpy	907	v "[what]"
victormenu_db387115	v	Okay! See you later.	game/script.rpy	924	v "[what]"
victoropinion_68493cd3	v	Yeah! I think a garden would be a great use of land for the neighborhood. It will let us grow heirloom produce that we can't find in stores.	game/script.rpy	933	v "[what]"
victoropinion_3990b1a2	v	A neighborhood garden would also give everybody access to fresh food, even if they don't have a lot of money to spend on groceries.	game/script.rpy	934	v "[what]"
victoropinion_3070a885	v	Since some neighborhoods don't have supermarkets, a garden would give more people healthy food options. And it can be fun to grow things yourself!	game/script.rpy	935	v "[what]"
heirloommenu_db387115	v	Okay! See you later.	game/script.rpy	950	v "[what]"
heirloom_a43d61f6	v	Heirloom fruits and vegetables are varieties of plants that have been passed down for many generations through seeds.	game/script.rpy	959	v "[what]"
heirloom_5b00d33e	v	Heirloom produce has unique colors, shapes, and flavors that you won't find at most grocery stores, because these types of plants aren't used in the big commercial farms that make most of our food.	game/script.rpy	960	v "[what]"
heirloom_a3ec9b18	v	Big farms use plants that make large, nice looking fruit, because it sells better at the store.	game/script.rpy	961	v "[what]"
heirloom_e82e2f11	v	Those big farm varieties are also bred to be more resistant to disease and weather, so the crops survive better.	game/script.rpy	962	v "[what]"
heirloom_b34cb4c5	v	But the tradeoff is that without heirloom versions of plants, we have less variety in tasty and unique flavors of produce.	game/script.rpy	963	v "[what]"
whyheirloom_f6f291b2	v	I really love the taste of heirloom fruits and veggies better. They're just extra juicy and have unique flavors.	game/script.rpy	967	v "[what]"
whyheirloom_bca87cae	v	Growing up, my family used heirloom plants that our neighbors grew to make my favorite foods, like the soup I want to make!	game/script.rpy	968	v "[what]"
whyheirloom_a32bad5a	v	So those different varieties of heirloom produce remind me of home. The grocery store versions just don't taste the same, if I can find them at all.	game/script.rpy	969	v "[what]"
gardenknowledge_c0d45ba2	v	Not at all! I've never grown anything before. But Wes said he would be happy to teach me.	game/script.rpy	973	v "[what]"
gardenknowledge_b647b707	v	I thought growing my own food would be too hard, but the community gardeners have lots of guides to help us figure out how to care for different kinds of plants.	game/script.rpy	974	v "[what]"
gardenfar_26e16640	v	No, it took me 45 minutes to get here on the bus. But I heard that the gardeners are trying to turn the empty lot near my house into a garden!	game/script.rpy	978	v "[what]"
gardenfar_da427c98	v	That lot is only a 10 minute walk from my apartment. If we had a garden there, it would be a lot easier for me to grown my own vegetables.	game/script.rpy	979	v "[what]"
wes_1_a0377c2e	w	Hey there! Welcome to the Westport Community Garden. Elliot called and said you might come by.	game/script.rpy	996	w "[what]"
wes_1_22c5c476	w	Feel free to explore the garden, and let me know if you are curious about anything.	game/script.rpy	997	w "[what]"
growing_food_40ad8daa	w	We grow all sorts of food here! Tomatoes, watermelon, zucchini, cucumbers, bell peppers, strawberries - the list goes on!	game/script.rpy	1022	w "[what]"
growing_food_61ea4529	w	Some of the plants, like tomatoes, we grow in containers, and others like the melons need more space to spread out.	game/script.rpy	1023	w "[what]"
growing_food_4efd276b	w	Growing your own food means the fruits and vegetables will be fresher and tastier, because they don't have to travel from other states or countries to get to your plate.	game/script.rpy	1024	w "[what]"
growing_food_832b6ed3	w	Homegrown fruits and vegetables are also good for our health because we can control the soil quality - and better soil means more nutritious produce.	game/script.rpy	1025	w "[what]"
garden_benefits_e90e574e	w	Absolutely! Gardens are really useful for people and for the insects and animals that live around here.	game/script.rpy	1030	w "[what]"
garden_benefits_663edefd	w	The people in the neighborhood can grow fresh fruits and vegetables, and all the different plants and flowers provide food for pollinators.	game/script.rpy	1031	w "[what]"
wes_pollen_fbb80816	w	Pollinators are creatures like bees and butterflies that transfer pollen from one flower to another.	game/script.rpy	1055	w "[what]"
wes_pollen_309c5983	w	This helps the plants reproduce and grow food - lots of plants can't grow their fruits without the help of pollinators!	game/script.rpy	1056	w "[what]"
types_pollinators_25dfc5c1	w	Honeybees are a particularly important pollinator for humans, because they pollinate a lot of the food crops that we grow.	game/script.rpy	1060	w "[what]"
types_pollinators_9a80a645	w	Flies, butterflies, birds, and even bats also pollinate particular types of flowers in different regions of the world.	game/script.rpy	1061	w "[what]"
types_pollinators_e6e5380d	w	But insects are definitely the most common pollinators when it comes to the foods that humans eat.	game/script.rpy	1062	w "[what]"
plants_help_e61d862f	w	Many pollinators, like honeybees, get food from plants by drinking flower nectar and eating pollen.	game/script.rpy	1066	w "[what]"
plants_help_87de4452	w	When the pollinators visit the plants, they move pollen from one part of the flower to another while they are gathering food.	game/script.rpy	1067	w "[what]"
plants_help_033c7528	w	It's a happy little accident - they're just trying to get food for themselves, but they end up helping us grow our food, too!	game/script.rpy	1068	w "[what]"
plants_help_8d9a12ad	w	Pollination helps the plants grow nice healthy fruits, which gives us yummy things to eat!	game/script.rpy	1069	w "[what]"
wes_plants_247b7005	w	Plants can be pollinated by wind, by insects and animals, and by people. This happens when pollen from a plant's flower is moved from the male part of the flower to the female part of the flower.	game/script.rpy	1073	w "[what]"
wes_plants_e49a2b73	w	People can pollinate some plants by using cotton swabs to help transfer pollen between flowers. This can be helpful when there aren't lots of pollinators around, but it takes a lot of time.	game/script.rpy	1074	w "[what]"
wes_plants_34a2a7a2	w	If we want to grow lots of food, it's better to have pollinators nearby who can help the plants grow healthy.	game/script.rpy	1075	w "[what]"
gardenquestions_0eebee75	w	What would you like to know about the garden?	game/script.rpy	1080	w "[what]"
gardenquestions_45d3cb67	w	Alright, just flag me down if you think of something.	game/script.rpy	1083	w "[what]"
bye_wes_d4197b48	w	It was great talking with you. Come by anytime, kid.	game/script.rpy	1114	w "[what]"
wes_2_6cc62741	w	Hope you're enjoying the garden, friend. Can I help with anything?	game/script.rpy	1123	w "[what]"
bye_wes2_faa711a6	w	No problem. Enjoy the garden!	game/script.rpy	1136	w "[what]"
wes_ca_25cf2c4f	w	What would you like to know?	game/script.rpy	1141	w "[what]"
wes_ca_38df314b	w	All good. Come find me if you have another question.	game/script.rpy	1144	w "[what]"
wes_ca_4f924fc4	w	Would you like to know anything else?	game/script.rpy	1169	w "[what]"
bees_chatting_dd2d0c52	narrator	There are lots of bees buzzing about as you approach the beehives. The beekeeper smiles warmly at you.	game/script.rpy	1193	narrator "[what]"
bees_chatting_5bf0177d	narrator	A small child is grinning and laughing as he watches the bees fly by. A worried-looking woman watches him carefully.	game/script.rpy	1194	narrator "[what]"
hivesregular_f1e5e3c7	narrator	Click the person you want to talk to, or click the map to travel somewhere else.	game/script.rpy	1200	narrator "[what]"
nadia_1_5920961f	n	Hi, I'm Nadia. I'm a beekeeper, though you can probably tell that from the outfit. I take care of the beehives in several community gardens around town.	game/script.rpy	1217	n "[what]"
nadia_1_f56d42ce	n	If you have any questions about bees, plants, and pollination, I'd be happy to tell you what I know.	game/script.rpy	1218	n "[what]"
beekeeper_1ceb18ec	n	I grew up on a farm, and I always thought bees were amazing. They're so small, but also so coordinated and intelligent!	game/script.rpy	1290	n "[what]"
beekeeper_5ab0e717	n	Did you know that bees communicate the locations of flowers to each other by dancing? How cool is that?	game/script.rpy	1291	n "[what]"
beekeeper_faeb7648	n	Anyway, bees are just such an important part of our ecosystem that I wanted to do something to help take care of them.	game/script.rpy	1292	n "[what]"
beekeeper_2d133066	n	Bees are important for pollinating lots of crops, such as almonds, apples, and blueberries. Without bees, many crops would have to be pollinated by hand, which would take a ton of time and money.	game/script.rpy	1293	n "[what]"
nadia_ca_65cbb4a0	n	Alright! Come back if you want to talk more about bees.	game/script.rpy	1300	n "[what]"
nadia_ca_bc545e10	n	Do you have any other questions?	game/script.rpy	1327	n "[what]"
bye_nadia_67da26bb	n	It was nice to meet you. Let me know if you have any more questions as you explore the garden!	game/script.rpy	1338	n "[what]"
nadia_2_d95b4f51	n	Hello dear! Can I help you with anything?	game/script.rpy	1345	n "[what]"
bye_nadia2_9110f921	n	No problem at all. Enjoy your visit!	game/script.rpy	1355	n "[what]"
x_1_6edd5f8c	x	Hi! Are you a gardener?	game/script.rpy	1372	x "[what]"
alex_visitor_f4dcf454	x	Us too! Mom says they might build a garden like this next door to our apartment building.	game/script.rpy	1383	x "[what]"
alex_visitor_102caa4e	x	I love the bees buzzing! Buzzzz buzzz buzzz...	game/script.rpy	1384	x "[what]"
alex_gardener_f49cfc2c	x	Whoa! Me too. I like worms. And dirt. And BEES!	game/script.rpy	1388	x "[what]"
gardenthink_41c52592	x	I like this garden! There's so many bees. Mom thinks they're creepy but I like them!	game/script.rpy	1409	x "[what]"
gardenthink_fd453234	x	And Wes gave me a tomato! It was yummy. Maybe I could grow big tomatoes like that if I was a gardener.	game/script.rpy	1410	x "[what]"
alex_lot_1c33c9b7	x	The big old dirt patch? Yeah. I throw rocks at the fence sometimes. Don't tell my mom.	game/script.rpy	1414	x "[what]"
alex_growfood_2912b65b	x	I don't know. Can you grow pizza in a garden?	game/script.rpy	1418	x "[what]"
alex_growfood_0d58eccf	x	Mom says she wants to grow spinach and tomatoes. Tomatoes are pizza! So we can grow part of the pizza.	game/script.rpy	1419	x "[what]"
alex_growfood_910bd358	x	I like blueberries too. We don't get the fresh ones lots but they're way juicier than the frozen bag ones.	game/script.rpy	1420	x "[what]"
bye_alex_9312dd08	x	Hahaha! Buzz you later!	game/script.rpy	1424	x "[what]"
sadkid_9874061d	x	Ohh...	game/script.rpy	1433	x "[what]"
x_2_04945857	x	Buzzzz... buzz buzz buzz!	game/script.rpy	1439	x "[what]"
alex_buzz_e9f190c7	x	There's a bee by your head. I think it likes you!	game/script.rpy	1447	x "[what]"
alex_buzz_1c356da6	t	Oh I love that kid. By the way, do you need any help? You can always click my button to say hi if you get bored!	game/script.rpy	1452	t "[what]"
cora_1_f3cd53a1	c	Oh Alex, be careful! Don't get too close to the hives! There's so many of them...	game/script.rpy	1476	c "[what]"
coranext_431e9e73	c	Goodness, no. I know they're good for the environment and all but...ugh. Bugs are too creepy and crawly. Alex loves them, though.	game/script.rpy	1483	c "[what]"
gentlebees_1a430621	c	Hm, well I'll have to take your word for it. I'm not becoming a beekeeper anytime soon.	game/script.rpy	1498	c "[what]"
gentlebees_40d86d21	c	I am curious about the garden though. They put up flyers all over our neighborhood about wanting to build another garden down the street from our apartment.	game/script.rpy	1499	c "[what]"
corathoughts_154cdeef	c	Other than the bees flying everywhere, it seems like a good place for the neighborhood.	game/script.rpy	1512	c "[what]"
corathoughts_d7742aa9	c	It's been really hard lately to get across town to get fresh fruits and vegetables from the store, since we don't have a car.	game/script.rpy	1513	c "[what]"
corathoughts_a5de36c7	c	And the stores just keep getting more expensive! My paycheck only goes so far. If we had a garden like this in our neighborhood, maybe I could grow some fresh food for the kids, y'know?	game/script.rpy	1514	c "[what]"
corathoughts_c3841750	c	I try my best to give them healthy things to eat, but on nights when I work late, I don't have time for much more than throwing a frozen meal in the microwave.	game/script.rpy	1515	c "[what]"
corathoughts_c61966cc	c	I don't know, maybe the garden would be just as tiring. But at least I would have food in my own backyard! That's more than we've got right now.	game/script.rpy	1516	c "[what]"
coragarden_605082ae	c	Oh! That's great. Will you tell the Mayor the families in the neighborhood want a garden too?	game/script.rpy	1529	c "[what]"
coragarden_4e8c58b6	c	Maybe we will get to grow our own food after all. Alex will be so excited! We can learn about growing fresh fruits and vegetables together.	game/script.rpy	1530	c "[what]"
coraparking_fba7bc9f	c	Oh. That won't really do anything for my family...we don't have a car anyway. I'd rather build something we can all use.	game/script.rpy	1536	c "[what]"
bye_cora_a23fac46	c	Thank you, dear. You too.	game/script.rpy	1542	c "[what]"
corastress_0f3aebf0	c	Oh it's alright, Alex is just - ALEX! Do not touch the bee!!	game/script.rpy	1560	c "[what]"
emptylot_a60c1394	narrator	The empty lot isn't much - just a wide patch of dirt. Elliot is exploring, likely imagining what a garden would look like here.	game/script.rpy	1583	narrator "[what]"
emptylot_2aa343d9	narrator	You see two men in suits sizing up the empty lot. You wonder what so many people are doing wandering around an empty bit of land.	game/script.rpy	1584	narrator "[what]"
emptylotregular_f1e5e3c7	narrator	Click the person you want to talk to, or click the map to travel somewhere else.	game/script.rpy	1590	narrator "[what]"
cy_1_c381b395	cy	Hey there, kiddo. Cyrus Murphy, Marketing Executive for CityPark.	game/script.rpy	1607	cy "[what]"
cy_1_e690eaf5	cy	Nice to meet ya.	game/script.rpy	1608	cy "[what]"
excited_cy_e666f0af	cy	It's great to see young people in this neighborhood so passionate about growth in their community!	game/script.rpy	1622	cy "[what]"
excited_cy_673511cb	cy	Our team at CityPark is looking forward to meeting more people like you while we get ready to build our new parking [structure].	game/script.rpy	1623	cy "[what]"
normal_cy_bf733fd6	cy	I'm glad so many folks have come by to say hello - our team at CityPark is all about working with the community.	game/script.rpy	1627	cy "[what]"
normal_cy_67ab525f	cy	Are you excited about the new parking [structure]?	game/script.rpy	1628	cy "[what]"
dislike_cy_8791f6a1	cy	Hey, I get it, you've got better things to do than talk with some stranger in a suit. But I look forward to getting to know you and your neighbors better as we begin construction!	game/script.rpy	1632	cy "[what]"
cy_pitch_e47bb816	cy	This empty lot here is the future site of a CityPark Park Express [structure]! It will be a prime location to encourage new businesses to move in on this street.	game/script.rpy	1652	cy "[what]"
cy_pitch_1c251dc5	cy	As soon as we get the sign-off from Mayor Watson, we're going to begin construction.	game/script.rpy	1653	cy "[what]"
agree_garage_c69e5a65	cy	That's what I'm talking about - you're a bright kid. Make sure to tell your friends all about CityPark and what a great choice we are for your neighborhood!	game/script.rpy	1667	cy "[what]"
dislike_garage_9d3ed42d	cy	Hey now, I know change can be scary, but just think about how much money the parking [structure] could make for the city!	game/script.rpy	1671	cy "[what]"
dislike_garage_0d34ee6a	cy	And that money can help fix roads, fund schools, and support the community. More parking means more businesses, more neighborhood growth - you're gonna love it, I swear.	game/script.rpy	1672	cy "[what]"
dislike_garage_52e7b219	el	We're NOT going to love it, Mr. Murphy. The [structure] might make money for you and your company, but the people here need food, not a place to park cars.	game/script.rpy	1682	el "[what]"
dislike_garage_5d3691fa	cy	Now Elliot, we've been over this! When we get this [structure] built, I'm sure a big grocery store will move right into town, and wouldn't you rather just go buy your food rather than having to spend all that time growing it?	game/script.rpy	1684	cy "[what]"
unsure_75047cb4	cy	It's a complex problem, kid. Perhaps you should learn more about it before you fall in with these gardeners.	game/script.rpy	1699	cy "[what]"
unsure_29c0fcf9	el	Ugh, ignore him. But it is a good idea to talk to the others in the neighborhood. We'll need their support to convince the Mayor!	game/script.rpy	1701	el "[what]"
grocery_7ab511f0	el	I know, it would be great if a grocery store moved in. But big chain stores don't usually move into low-income neighborhoods like this one because they don't think they'll make enough money.	game/script.rpy	1709	el "[what]"
grocery_b2996d2b	el	I'm not convinced a parking [structure] will change that.	game/script.rpy	1710	el "[what]"
grocery_65ab72c0	cy	You never know until you try! We've been gathering economic data on how parking [structure]s impact neighborhood growth. You'll need a lot of evidence to beat our pitch to the Mayor, kid.	game/script.rpy	1712	cy "[what]"
cy_challenge_8e66bed7	el	That's right! We're working hard to build a persuasive argument for the Mayor to support the community garden project.	game/script.rpy	1723	el "[what]"
cy_challenge_d7d0288a	cy	Alright kiddo, whatever you say. Best of luck, and may the best argument win.	game/script.rpy	1725	cy "[what]"
bye_cyrus_4782dc84	cy	Great talking with you, kiddo! Take it easy.	game/script.rpy	1732	cy "[what]"
cy_2_ee39fcf5	cy	Ah, our resident investigator, back again. What can I do for you?	game/script.rpy	1739	cy "[what]"
garage_benefits_600ad6f0	cy	Ah, so you're coming around to our plan? Wonderful!	game/script.rpy	1756	cy "[what]"
garage_benefits_9bfd2b8a	cy	Parking [structure]s can be great for local businesses. If people from out of town can easily park in the neighborhood, then more people will stop here and spend money on shopping trips.	game/script.rpy	1757	cy "[what]"
garage_benefits_6b14d564	cy	More parking means more businesses can move in, which makes the economy of the neighborhood stronger! It might even bring new jobs to the area.	game/script.rpy	1758	cy "[what]"
cy_pollution_7d30273d	cy	Oh, cars are everywhere. One more [structure] won't change anything. The pollution isn't as important as the money the [structure] will make for the city.	game/script.rpy	1762	cy "[what]"
cy_pollution_53d915c6	cy	That's the spirit. CityPark will make this neighborhood a shopping hotspot for the city!	game/script.rpy	1769	cy "[what]"
cy_bees_073df705	cy	What about them? The bees can just go somewhere else to find flowers. We should care more about the people here, and making the local economy stronger.	game/script.rpy	1773	cy "[what]"
bye_cyrus2_289bbad1	cy	Alright then. Tell your friends to sign up for our CityPark newsletter!	game/script.rpy	1778	cy "[what]"
mayor_1_39805a9a	m	Hello there! I'm Mayor Watson. I'm out here today gathering community opinions on the empty lot.	game/script.rpy	1794	m "[what]"
mayor_1_4f337e5e	m	Do you have any thoughts about it?	game/script.rpy	1795	m "[what]"
garden_m_d8d193a4	m	Ah, interesting. The garden would provide some food for the neighborhood, though the parking [structure] might be more financially useful for the city.	game/script.rpy	1806	m "[what]"
garden_m_2357b9b2	m	I need to consider the research and figure out what is best for our community.	game/script.rpy	1807	m "[what]"
parking_m_701f91e2	m	Oh really? I do think the parking [structure] would give the city some useful income that we could use to improve our schools.	game/script.rpy	1811	m "[what]"
parking_m_100cf046	m	But the Community Gardeners feel strongly that a garden would be more beneficial to the neighborhood.	game/script.rpy	1812	m "[what]"
parking_m_2357b9b2	m	I need to consider the research and figure out what is best for our community.	game/script.rpy	1813	m "[what]"
uncertain_m_68bf7055	m	That's okay, I'm not sure either! I'm going to talk with the Community Gardeners and the CityPark representative to see what kind of data they have for their proposals.	game/script.rpy	1817	m "[what]"
mayor_request_c07abdb9	m	If you gather any information you think I'd find interesting, feel free to come back and let me know!	game/script.rpy	1821	m "[what]"
mayor_2_d51e9435	m	Hello there! What can I do for you?	game/script.rpy	1828	m "[what]"
what_evidence_0d572fa6	m	I want to gather many different kinds of evidence. Opinions of the community members, but also concrete information about how the garden and the parking [structure] will impact the community.	game/script.rpy	1839	m "[what]"
what_evidence_2f6df93b	m	Scientific evidence about how the garden would impact the environment would be convincing. It would also be helpful to gather data about economic and health impacts on the community.	game/script.rpy	1840	m "[what]"
what_evidence_1b5bfeee	m	Gathering information from different sources will make for a more convincing argument. I know CityPark has been gathering lots of data to persuade me to support their plan.	game/script.rpy	1841	m "[what]"
good_argument_0bbe21bb	m	A persuasive argument brings together many different types of evidence and tells a good story about why someone should agree with your point of view.	game/script.rpy	1850	m "[what]"
good_argument_7cad7190	m	If I am going to support the Community Garden project, I need to know how the garden will benefit the people in the community.	game/script.rpy	1851	m "[what]"
good_argument_88ae5b39	m	I also need to be convinced that the benefits of the garden are more important than the money and business that the parking [structure] will bring.	game/script.rpy	1852	m "[what]"
mayor_eval_edee51c8	m	I'd love to hear it. What have you found?	game/script.rpy	1861	m "[what]"
mayor_eval_4693ca86	m	That's alright. Come back when you're ready to share your ideas.	game/script.rpy	1865	m "[what]"
bye_mayor_3e487b1a	m	Thank you for sharing your ideas with me. Engaged citizens make our community stronger!	game/script.rpy	1921	m "[what]"
continue_search_b98e32ac	m	Wonderful. I look forward to hearing your argument when it is ready to share.	game/script.rpy	1927	m "[what]"
elliot_chatting_ff2cd735	el	Welcome back! Did you find some interesting evidence for us to use in our pitch to the mayor?	game/script.rpy	1939	el "[what]"
still_investigating_ad063ab3	el	The sign of a great investigator is knowing when you need to learn more!	game/script.rpy	1948	el "[what]"
still_investigating_8e2abd72	el	The folks over at the Food Lab know a lot about soil and nutrients, so they could probably help us figure out what kind of evidence we need to gather to convince the mayor.	game/script.rpy	1949	el "[what]"
still_investigating_8f45fc09	el	And the gardeners at the community garden across town know a whole lot about bees and plants. They could tell us more about what benefits a garden can bring to a neighborhood.	game/script.rpy	1950	el "[what]"
still_investigating_9c13e56a	el	When you feel like you've gathered enough info to present our persuasive argument to the mayor, let me or Riley know, and we can workshop together!	game/script.rpy	1951	el "[what]"
ideasharing_a5ffc5e8	el	Sweet. So pretend I'm the mayor! Hey there good citizen! What do you think about this garden idea? Should I support it?	game/script.rpy	1956	el "[what]"
ideasharing_9e20be56	el	That's okay! Come back when you're ready to try out an argument.	game/script.rpy	1959	el "[what]"
ideasharing_e4c51900	el	Are there other ideas you want to run by me?	game/script.rpy	1995	el "[what]"
ideasharing_d0baa81c	el	Okay! Let me know if you find new evidence later!	game/script.rpy	2001	el "[what]"
tulip_endgame_8ffe09a1	t	Great job sharing your ideas with the Mayor! How do you think it went?	game/script.rpy	2019	t "[what]"
tulip_endgame_31e5fa4b	t	Nice work sharing your argument! There are more folks around town we should talk to - let's make sure we include evidence from lots of different sources to be extra convincing!	game/script.rpy	2022	t "[what]"
tulip_endgame_5ab6623a	t	Wonderful! You've been chatting with lots of different folks to improve your argument. Why don't you try taking some more notes in your notebook so we remember all of the most important parts of your argument?	game/script.rpy	2025	t "[what]"
needmore_3eef22bc	t	That's okay! Don't be discouraged. A strong argument is going to need evidence from different sources, and it needs to cover different layers of the problem.	game/script.rpy	2038	t "[what]"
needmore_bd092bff	t	This empty lot decision is going to impact people, bees like me, and the environment. As you talk to folks, think about what layers might be missing in your argument.	game/script.rpy	2039	t "[what]"
maybeconvinced_1a83db7f	t	That's a good sign! I wonder if there are pieces of evidence in your notebook that you could add to your argument to make it more specific?	game/script.rpy	2044	t "[what]"
maybeconvinced_c77ff4e1	t	You're on the right track, then! Maybe there are a few more pieces of evidence you can gather in your notebook to make your argument more persuasive.	game/script.rpy	2047	t "[what]"
convinced_endprep_4ac8d0d5	t	Amazing! I'm so glad.	game/script.rpy	2051	t "[what]"
ending_game_b5281379	t	If you are satisfied with your persuasive argument, we can end the game and see what happens to the empty lot.	game/script.rpy	2055	t "[what]"
ending_game_0abac2da	t	But if you want to try to make your argument even more persuasive, you can keep exploring for a while and end the game later.	game/script.rpy	2056	t "[what]"
ending_game_575c56e6	t	What do you want to do?	game/script.rpy	2057	t "[what]"
ending_game_67364388	t	Okay! I bet you can find even more evidence for your notebook if you talk with more people!	game/script.rpy	2061	t "[what]"
ending_game_2581533c	t	Okay! Oooo, I'm so excited to see what happens, I'm practically buzzing with excitement!	game/script.rpy	2064	t "[what]"
final_garden_96c29895	el	We did it! Thanks to all of your help, we were able to convince Mayor Watson to build a community garden for the neighborhood.	game/script.rpy	2082	el "[what]"
final_garden_593206e9	r	The garden is becoming a favorite hangout spot for everyone. Wes has been coming here to teach workshops on how to care for the plants, and our first harvest is almost ready!	game/script.rpy	2087	r "[what]"
final_garden_fff1204d	c	You know, I had my doubts about the bees, but the garden has been really good for the neighborhood. The air even feels fresher around here!	game/script.rpy	2101	c "[what]"
final_garden_52a397c0	x	Wes is teaching me how to grow tomatoes! We planted some seeds in the spring, and now they're HUGE!	game/script.rpy	2103	x "[what]"
final_garden_f25cbe02	v	Wes is such a great teacher! I've been learning too, and the veggies are almost ready for soup season!	game/script.rpy	2108	v "[what]"
final_garden_ec46896b	t	The garden has been wonderful for the bees, too! Nadia helped the community plant some native flowers, so we have lots of tasty food to choose from.	game/script.rpy	2122	t "[what]"
final_garden_806ebf33	t	It seems like the people here are really happy to have fresh, healthy food to grow in their backyard! You should be proud of all the work you did to convince the mayor that this was the best plan.	game/script.rpy	2123	t "[what]"
final_garden_502bd2a1	t	I'll see you around, human friend. Thanks for bee-ing a part of our community! Hehe.	game/script.rpy	2124	t "[what]"
final_parking_94805219	cy	Look at that beautiful parking [structure]! See kid, I told you this would be a great addition to the neighborhood.	game/script.rpy	2143	cy "[what]"
final_parking_61e3feaf	m	This really has been a great economic investment for the neighborhood. More people from out of town are visiting, which has been great for the local businesses.	game/script.rpy	2145	m "[what]"
final_parking_c886b393	el	Well, I guess the mayor is happy with his choice. A grocery store never moved in though, so it feels like this is good for business but not really good for the people who live here.	game/script.rpy	2156	el "[what]"
final_parking_cd7f91a0	c	We don't own a car, so the parking [structure] hasn't done much for us. The streets are also so busy now that I worry about Alex playing outside.	game/script.rpy	2161	c "[what]"
final_parking_5703d324	t	Hmm, it seems like some folks are happy with the parking [structure], but it didn't solve all the problems.	game/script.rpy	2172	t "[what]"
final_parking_e4cb4634	t	For the bees, there isn't a lot of green space left around here, so we won't find much food. The air is also getting a little polluted lately.	game/script.rpy	2173	t "[what]"
final_parking_74bdb6db	t	We're going to head out and find a different neighborhood to explore that might have more food for us.	game/script.rpy	2174	t "[what]"
final_parking_d7769bc0	t	Thanks for bee-ing my human friend! Hehe. I'll see you around!	game/script.rpy	2175	t "[what]"
end_137d2edd	narrator	Thanks for playing! Raise your hand to let the researchers know that you're finished.	game/script.rpy	2180	narrator "[what]"
